Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 1:46 PM; Case called for Hearing. Prosecuting attorney Alyssa M Jay in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Christopher M Przeracki not in court.  Attorney Timothy T. Kay in court for Christopher M Przeracki.  Atty. Wang, who represents the defendant in 21CF1607 & 22CF127, provides an update, she advises that neither her nor Atty. Kay have an explanation for the defendant's non-appearance today.  Court notes that the defendant was aware of today's hearing and has failed to appear today, as well the defendant continues to be non-compliant with WCS.  Based on all of that the Court will issue a capias and orders bail be forfeited.

Ext Code #3.
Bail jumping on underlying Waukesha County case 21CF1607.

10:06 AM; Case called for Bail/bond hearing. Prosecuting attorney Shawn N Woller in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Christopher M Przeracki not in court.  Attorney Angela Wang in court for Christopher M Przeracki.  Atty. Wang advises she has been in contact with her client and he was not aware of this hearing date today, and believed he only needed to appear at the status hearing set for 9/7/2022.  Atty. Wang notes the defendant has been accepted in to treatment court so she is asking the court to stay a capias until the next court date on 09/07/2022.  Due to non-appearance today and the WCS non-compliance State is asking for warrant or bail be increased.  Atty. Wang presents additional statements and notes parties have reached a global resolution on all matters, but only this case has WCS monitoring.  Court will authorize but stay the issuance of a capias until the next court date set for 09/07/2022 at 1:30 p.m.

10:12 AM; Case called for  Defendant Christopher M Przeracki in court with attorney Angela Wang.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern Nikole Kane appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Atty.
